                             <a href="/3061-18" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">
                                <span class="tei-persName">Eusebius</span> 
                                was a stweard.
                             <a href="/3061-19" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">
                            Severus 
                            was bishop over
                            Eusebius and 
                            Victor.
                         <a href="/3061-17" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">
                            Severus sent 
                            Eusebius and 
                            Victor to urge
                            Marinus to repent 
                            and abandon his Eutychian views of the incarnation.
                            
                                
                            
